{
  "stem": "11611.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of these defendants got an eight-year sentence, and one got a 15-year sentence.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the real result was that they were both out of jail pretty quickly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Puhl, I think, became a member of the board of the Dresdner Bank-- and I think he owed his subsequent career to me, because I put him in the same dock.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably three months or so, but a fair amount of the time was taken up with the case of this stateless--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Translator, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, Werber?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, Werber was a-- strictly devoted to working on these cases when I knew him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very friendly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, he was basically an investigator and an interpreter for me on the bank cases.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Subsequently, he moved back to Vienna, which was his native place.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He then became a spy for the Russians-- along with a fair number of people who worked as interpreters at Nuremberg, who became spies for the CIA.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They used to deal with each other, you know , dicker.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at one time, Werber must have gotten out of the accomplished negotiations, because I picked up a morning newspaper-- I was working in Washington with a law firm then, Paul Weiss-- and the big headline, 'Germans Brought to the States for Espionage Charges.' And I took a look at it, and I started to read the article, and there was Werber, and his brother-in-law, who was also at Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I thought, uh-oh, I'm now in for it, because the only lawyer he knows in Washington is me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I went to my office, and by noon I had a call from the jail.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
